Package org.openhab.core.config.discovery

Class DiscoveryServiceRegistryOSGiTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhab.core.test.java.JavaTest
      • org.openhab.core.test.java.JavaOSGiTest
        • org.openhab.core.config.discovery.DiscoveryServiceRegistryOSGiTest
  • public class DiscoveryServiceRegistryOSGiTest
extends JavaOSGiTest
    The DiscoveryServiceRegistryOSGiTest test checks if the concrete DiscoveryServiceRegistry implementation tracks all registered DiscoveryServices and if a registered listener is notified about the events fired by the accordingDiscoveryService.

    This implementation creates two DiscoveryService mocks and registers them as service at the OSGi service registry. Since this test creates DiscoveryResults which are added to the Inbox, the Inbox is cleared again after this test returns.

    Author:
    Michael Grammling - Initial contribution, Simon Kaufmann - added tests for ExtendedDiscoveryService, ported to Java, Andre Fuechsel - added tests for removeOlderResults for a specific bridge only
